@startuml 11-sequence-ml-prediction
title ML Prediction Flow

actor User
participant "Frontend / Agent" as Client
participant "API Gateway" as API
participant "ML Service\n(vessel-delay-prediction)" as ML
participant "Model Registry\n(joblib / GCS)" as Model
database "Feature Store\n(Postgres / BigQuery)" as Features
participant "Kafka" as Kafka

User -> Client : Request delay prediction\nfor incoming vessel
Client -> API : POST /ml/vessel-delay/predict\nBearer JWT

API -> API : RBAC check (ml:predict)
API -> ML : POST /predict\n{vessel_type, origin,\nweather_score, congestion_level}

ML -> Features : (optional) fetch\nhistorical features
Features --> ML : feature vector

ML -> Model : load_model()\nGradientBoostingRegressor
Model --> ML : trained model

ML -> ML : predict(X)\n→ delay hours
ML -> Kafka : publish prediction event
ML --> API : PredictionResponse\n{prediction, confidence, model_version}

API --> Client : 200 OK
Client --> User : "Predicted delay: 4.2 hours\n(confidence: 82%)"

note over ML
  ML Services (ports 8300-8306):
  • vessel-delay-prediction
  • berth-optimization
  • crane-failure-prediction
  • truck-queue-prediction
  • congestion-prediction
  • anomaly-detection
  • revenue-forecasting
end note

@enduml
